properties.name: Along watershed divide from head of Shaw Creek
properties.description: On Royce's (1887) map, the boundary line appears to generally follow a watershed divide from the head of Shaw Creek to a point where a trail intersects this ridge, near the head of the North Fork of the Edisto River.

properties.name: Straight line to Broad River
properties.description: Royce's (1887) map shows a straight line between the point where the boundary line intersects a trail and the point where it meets the Broad River. If such a line was ever surveyed, no trace of it seems to remain.

properties.name: Along the Broad and Congaree Rivers
properties.description: According to Royce's (1887) map, this portion of the boundary line follows the Broad River downstream to the confluence with the Saluda River and then downstream along the Congaree River to the mouth of the Wateree River.

properties.surveyors: Edward Wilkinson, John Pickins, Alexander Cameron, six Cherokee chiefs

properties.name: Santee River to Edisto River
properties.description: Referencing a 1721 map by John Senex, Royce describes the boundary line between the English and Indians as “pursuing a southwesterly course” from the Santee River to the Edisto River, “which, as near as can be ascertained, was at the junction of the North and South Edisto.”

properties.name: South Fork Edisto River to the headwaters of Shaw's Creek
properties.description: "Following from thence up the South Edisto to its source..." inferred from map to be the headwaters of Shaw's Creek.

properties.name: Headwaters of Shaw's Creek to the mouth of Stevens Creek
properties.description: "...the boundary pursued a southwesterly course, striking the Savannah River in the vicinity of the mouth of Stevens Creek..." Mapped by me to follow a drainage divide.

properties.name: Savannah River to the Great Buffalo Lick
properties.description: According to Royce's map, the boundary follows the Broad River, Long Creek, and Buffalo Creek.
